session_id: Session identifier for request header\n92:             code: Code to execute\n93:             language: Programming language (default: \"python\")\n94:             timeout: Optional timeout override in seconds. If None, uses\n95:                     instance default timeout.\n96:         \n97:         Returns:\n98:             requests.Response object from the POST request\n99:         \n100:         Raises:\n101:             requests.HTTPError: On HTTP error status codes\n102:             requests.RequestException: On network errors\n103:         \"\"\"\n104:         headers = {\n105:             self.SESSION_HEADER: session_id,\n106:             \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n107:         }\n108:         \n109:         payload = {\n110:             \"code\": code,\n111:             \"language\": language,\n112:         }\n113:         \n114:         if timeout is None:\n115:             effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n116:         else:\n117:             effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, timeout)\n118:         \n119:         url = urljoin(self.base_url, \"execute/\")\n120:         \n121:         self.logger.debug(f\"POST {url} with payload: {payload}\")\n122:         \n123:         response = self.session.post(\n124:             url,\n125:             json=payload,\n126:             headers=headers,\n127:             timeout=effective_timeout,\n128:         )\n129:         \n130:         response.raise_for_status()\n131:         return response\n132:     \n133:     def upload_file(\n134:         self,\n135:         session_id: str,\n136:         file_path: str,\n137:         file_content: bytes,\n138:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n139:     ) -> requests.Response:\n140:         \"\"\"Upload a file to the code interpreter session.\n141:         \n142:         Args:\n143:             session_id: Session identifier for request header\n144:             file_path: Path/filename for the uploaded file\n1